# News Topic Classification using RNN, LSTM, GRU and Bi-LSTM

## Project Overview

This project compares four recurrent neural network architectures for multi-class news topic classification using the AG News dataset.

Models Evaluated:

- Simple RNN
- LSTM
- GRU
- Bi-LSTM

## Dataset

AG News Dataset

Classes:
- World
- Sports
- Business
- Science/Technology

Training Samples: 120,000

Testing Samples: 7,600

## Data Preprocessing

- Lowercase conversion
- Punctuation removal
- Stopword removal
- Tokenization
- Sequence padding

## Model Results

| Model | Accuracy |
|---------|---------|
| RNN | 81.22% |
| LSTM | 25.00% |
| GRU | 25.26% |
| Bi-LSTM | 90.54% |

## Key Findings

- Bi-LSTM achieved the highest classification accuracy.
- RNN provided strong baseline performance.
- LSTM and GRU failed to converge effectively under the current experimental setup.
- Bi-LSTM demonstrated superior contextual understanding of news articles.

## Technologies Used

- Python
- TensorFlow
- Keras
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-Learn
- Matplotlib
- NLTK

